<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>It&#39;s <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Week">Golden Week</a> in Japan, when the Japan Chess Championship is traditionally held. The format is a 9-round Swiss with 90+30 time control.</p> <p>A rather large number of qualifier tournaments resulted in 67 competitors fighting for the national title. There are 10 titled players (excluding arena titles), including 2 IMs and the <a href="https://ratings.fide.com/profile/12401404">highest-rated Candidate Master</a> in the world.</p> <p>After 5 rounds, we have 2 players with a perfect score: IM Nanjo Ryosuke and FM Aoshima Mirai, who&#39;s also a 6-dan ranked professional shogi player.</p> <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=03qpAlQ5lHU">Link</a> for the 6th round broadcast.</p> <p><a href="https://chess-results.com/tnr734613.aspx?lan=1&amp;turdet=YES">Results and standings on chess-results</a></p> <p><a href="https://www.chess.com/events/2023-japan-chess-championship/games">Event page on chess.com (including games)</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/nandemo"> /u/nandemo </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/chess/comments/138db63/the_japan_chess_championship_2023_is_underway/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/chess/comments/138db63/the_japan_chess_championship_2023_is_underway/">[comments]</a></span>